caption: This is one of my favorite additions to our neighborhood in years! The staff is fantastic and knows every single thing on the shelves, and while there is a small selection it is kind of everything that you need. The wine choices are on point, and they are happy to help you pick out a bottle to go with the food that they make in their ovens, which I highly recommend! They work with a lot of local purveyors, so I get my local coffee, my local milk, and even pick up my hyperlocal CSA produce right there. They are amazingly welcoming to my dog and my daughter, and so it is a pleasure to go in there every time.
Underrated pizza spot in DC.  Great, albeit small, craft beer selection.
They actually cook their pizzas in a brick oven, so the crust is cooked great and produces some of the best pizza in DC! Very friendly staff and local beers available.

OMG. I love this place. I would buy toilet paper and sweat pants here if they sold it. But luckily, they don't. They are a boutique store and they don't do everything, but everything they do, they do well. Best pizza in town. Amazing bread, meats, and baking supplies (e.g., fresh milled flour). Don't come here looking for a broad selection, but know that what they have is carefully selected and high quality. They also have an awesome beer and wine selection, and the wine is at a very attractive price point. If my wife and I ever move, being closer to Old City would be a selling point for the house!
Nice store I use to stop by before work.
Great pizza, and an impressive wine, beer, and soda selection.

After living in the Union Market/H street area for over a year, I've finally find my 1st choice pizza spot.  Not only do they have amazing pizza, but they have about anything else you could want as well.  Incredible corner store that is worth the visit.
Really great pizza!! Neighborhood gem and solid market items too.

The staff are friendly. They have a variety of drink and order to eat food, espially there pizzas. They also partner with plant companies to sell in there store as well. I would recommend going and supporting small businesses in the area
Love this place!
Hands-down the pizza crust in the city, plus some great unusual topping combinations.

Spent the weekend at DC, got the American pizza, spicy crab Mac and cheese and regular salad mix. Great food and a great price! The service was great and the shop has an overall very hip and nice environment. Def recommend.
Some of the best, fresh, homemade food in this neighborhood.  Don't overlook it!!
the pizza and baguettes are splendid.
Still the best pizza on the Hill.
The food is made with so much care.  The salads delicious with depth.  The lamb skewers excellent.  My neighbors say that the pizzas are incredible.  I wish I had started eating here before.
Best pizza in the city! I am definitely going back for more.
Friendly staff and helpful staff and a great place to relax
We love Old City Market. The food is great. The bread is to die for. And the staff knows us by name.
A good place to chill
Great place to have in the neighborhood! Awesome pizza, good beer selection, and friendly staff.
Fun spot with great pizza! The pizza combinations were so fun and tasted great. Staff were incredibly kind. Definitely visit!
Service is always great and so is the food!
Great food, product selection, and people!
They have georgian wines!
Awesome people and great food and beverage selection.
Great find. Good daily specials. Coworkers enjoyed the pot pies, empanadas, and sandwiches we ordered.

This place has EVERYTHING. Food, coffee, wine, convenience store items, PLANTS?! And it’s all really high quality and fairly priced! Not only that, but the people who work there all seem super nice and helpful. 10/10 would recommend for pretty much anything.
Great
Killer Wings!  Big, Smokey, & Savory with the hint of heat. Crispy crunchy and chewy crust. Good sauce, not overpowered by toppings.
My daughter loves the hot chocolate here
Wow!!! They make some awesome pizza!!
Great, eclectic grocery, gift, entertainment place. Best pizza in town!
We love this community gem with good home cooked food, friendly environment, coffee and a relaxed homely basement to sit for a while with a good book.
Delicious pizza.  Super-friendly staff.
Great neighborhood market shop with fresh pastries and fabulous pizza! Check them out if you need a pint of Ben and Jerry's, a new plant from Lovers plant shop, or some fig jam!
Amazing place, amazing people, amazing food!
The food was delicious. Super NICE, and down-to-earth people! They even went way out of their way, to help me navigate my way through the city. Food- 5stars Customer Service- 5+stars

My wife and I love to get sandwiches and other takeout from this jewel on 6th street a few blocks from the H street corridor and Union Market. The staff are extremely friendly and welcoming. Wine tastings are hosted here and it has an authentic feel as a neighborhood hangout. The place is also spotless and carries some local brands as well. Off-menu items are fantastic and we had a stuffed squid dish that was so delicious that we went and ordered another the very next day. Well worth a visit...or two.

This is a great space but, the young man working the counter was rude to a customer and snapped on him the last time I was there. He seemed flustered about getting his daughter to school, which the customer had no way of knowing. Very unprofessional we all hv things going on in life but we should treat each other respectfully

Everything at OCM is fantastic. The people, Curt [owner], who's always helping someone solve some radom neighborhood issue. The food, homemade dinners with hyper-locally sourced ingredients. The space, especially the downstairs dining room with record player [+100 records] and baby grand piano.

Very disappointed regarding the way I was spoken to today regarding a misunderstanding. The owner shook his finger in my face to chastise me as if I were a child without asking me what happened. Whether you agree with a customer or not, they should not be spoken to in this way.

Nice, friendly corner store.  Sells what any local market would sell as well as great food and spirits.  You can dine on site which is a plus.  Many different delicacies to choose from and premium wine is available.

This place is a delight. I’ve been here twice in the past week. Great food, service, art and setup. It’s a homey feel— that’s what I love most. If you’re into supporting local businesses, support this one!!
Great place to get real food with a nice atmosphere. I stop anytime I'm in DC nice beer selection too.
Very nice lamb. Was told to try the chicken skewer sandwich and I will.....next time.
What a sweet, friendly little neighborhood shop! Great service. Found a great deal on a bottle of wine and some other goodies. Lots of gluten free options, including pizza!
Great food, Service and CLEAN!! Not the Corner Store anymore
Great food
Put this place on the list of things to do!

Received a NIFT giftcard for this restaurant and called to place my order in. On the phone I was greeted by a friendly voice and recognized it when I picked up my veggie tacos (YUMMY). (I'm sorry I don't remember his name) He offered me a sample of banana bread and showed me the other desserts. I enjoyed the small mom and pop shop feel & awesome customer service. I will definitely come again.
Love it
Chicken kabobs are fantastic. Service is excellent
Excellent pizzas.  Incredible customer service and great eclectic local offerings.
(Translated by Google) Best Pizza in Washington !!!  (Original) Beste Pizza in Washington!!!

The owners are caring; they hire staff who care about their job; it truly feels like a family market in the neighborhood. Now they have an up and coming premier wine sommelier planning out their wine stock. The veggie options are better than any of the other veg restaurants in the area... Yeah you would not expect it!!
Great pizza.  Great counter.
very unique and charming. Very friendly staff. Food was excellent (lamb meatballs)
Great community eatery with endless options
Really delicious food, fun atmosphere (especially the downstairs), and a great place to shop and eat.

I ordered the Cajun shrimp pizza. Didn’t really care for it, it had too much goat cheese which over powered the flavor. Made it extremely bitter. It also didn’t taste “Cajun” lol. The crust was good and the food was served hot. Also got a chicken panini and it was okay. Would go back to try another menu item to see if I have better luck.

I love the place it's right by my house the woman who owns it is always very pleasant and very helpful I would go there more but the gentleman that is there most of the time is rude and acts like your bothering him. I only gave 5 stars because of the owner and the place is always very clean and neat.
Very good food. Love the pizza

I'm obsessed with their pizza. The tomato sauce and crust is PERFECT for me and very flavorful. They do an amazing charcuterie (good cheeses, nut selection, olives) and I love their potato wedges (with a bit of spice).  I've only ordered delivery and called once and received super friendly customer service.
Pizza has gotten better. Super friendly

A hidden gem! Fantastic artisan pizzas, in a delightfully odd space that sells everything from children's play sets to vinyl records to local art to groceries  The owner is incredibly friendly and genuine

Cute, somewhat excentric little market. Really welcoming staff. Loved the mix of items for sale in the downstairs, including African fabric, and the piano. You can find  bday cards, muffins, chips, pizza, wine and more. Haven't ordered food yet, but read GREAT reviews of the pizza.
Great pizza and really friendly staff (thanks Kurt!). We ordered the Mediterranean and Pear Pair pizza and Greek salad. All three was delicious.
Good place to eat out and take out. But limited parking space.
Great place to do work, excellent iced coffee with frozen coffee ice cubes!

Tried the breakfast calzone and it was awesome. The oven kept the dough soft on the inside with a crisp exterior and the ingredients were flavorful and fresh. Care was put into preparing the ingredients and the construction. Also the atmosphere was calm and laid back, capturing the corner store market perfectly.

We were highly impressed with the quality and service.  We just flew in from Oregon walked to this cute store and the people  were so friendly.  Especially the lady at the counter. She gave us great city advice and extra sauces & cheeses for our meal for free.  We forgot them and she walked to our Airbnb to give them to us.  That's what I say is over and above great service.  Side note food was great! This is a must visit!
Yummy pizza, friendly staff!
Lovely people and food
had wonderful experience here. Great food and coffee, and very nice owner. I love the basement library, a very quiet place to study.
Great food from great people.
Such a friendly place! Exactly what a neighborhood corner market should be. Pet friendly too

Super cool local market with a store for staples, toys, gifts and music in the basement. Great pizza and deli with a nice wine and beer selection upstairs. Occasional cool activities like music and wine tasting. Coffee and pastries as well!
Try the roasted red pepper soup.  It's the greatest!

Great local market... They get their bread from the former Baker at marvelous market. They have very reasonable wine, great food made in the shop and a good set of groceries. Not a large selection or brands but the brands they do carry are curated well.
Excellent service. Variety sit or carryout with mom and pop neighborhood welcoming atmosphere

I want to love this place because it's so close to my house, but I can't quite say it's a 5 star experience. They have some random grocery items, but more snacks than basics- ie no loaves of bread (when I've checked). There is one employee who has overcharged me almost every time I've ordered a coffee from the cafe and when I ask if it's the price listed corrects it without saying anything. It's awkward.

In town on business, I had several coworkers recommend Old City Market and Oven and it is down the street from work. Stopped in, greeted by Mary at the counter, a very pleasant, kind and friendly lady, treated me like I was a visiting family member, she made suggestions and if I didn’t see something or she did not know the answer she found out for me. As I was looking around ( selection on the shelves is limited but excellent, there is a good variety of homemade food though) I realized Mary genuinely treated each customer in the same manner. I ordered two pizzas and as a native New Yorker I was pleasantly surprised at the quality of the pies, the tomato, mozzarella and chorizo was excellent, the second pie pesto, ricotta and spinach was very good as well. Looking forward to many more visits and trying other dishes . Highly recommended
Good people,  community, food, coffee, wine, beer, gifts, art, books... etc!

This is a great place to bring the kids for a nice bit after school, or a for a lovely personal little date with your love bug. They sale wines and on Wednesdays its 10% off I don't know how long that last but its great because I got a really nice wine today. They also have a spot downstairs to relax and eat with a piano. Lovely place and the Lamb pizza is my favorite

Awesome pizza and wine collection and very well priced too. They have every day discount wines and a great deli if you are in need of charcuterie too. The books and gifts section downstairs is phenomenal great for gifts!
Lovely place

Great food & service with staff who care & know the community in NOMA area. Please support our local shops & markets so we can continue to receive this high quality of goods & service at a low price in our neighborhoods.
Great pizza and good selection of wine. Interesting items in the shop downstairs. Just allow ample time, can sometimes be slow and wait for food.
Get the fresh flat bread!
Awesome food. Great selection of local products. Fun! Come!
Records. Calzone. Expresó. Need i say more?
This place is great.  the pizza is fantastic and the atmosphere is warm and friendly .  It is just the kind of place every neighborhood needs.

It's a great little homegrown place new to the neighborhood and really tasty food It's kind of an overgrown coffee shop replete with a progressive attitude Locally owned Locally run I expect to plan my operations of social justice here! 🤓
Wonderful, excellent food with delightful and engaging service. I'd be a regular if I lived nearby!
Amazing pizza and friendly staff. Thank you!
Pizza and sandwiches are fantastic, plus staple groceries with no line.
Come here for pizza cooked by a master.  Real wood fired oven quality.  Their wine to go section is great, and you gotta love the local character...check out the eclectic art downstairs.

Excellent made to order pizza with fresh ingredients. I recommend the tomato base with mozzarella and chorizo.  Also great wine and beer selection.  My wife loves the coffee. Fair prices. Nice owners and staff.  Great addition to the neighborhood!
